.TH "usb_enable_endpoint" 9 "usb_enable_endpoint" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_enable_endpoint \- Enable an endpoint for USB communications
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_enable_endpoint
.BI "(struct usb_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct usb_host_endpoint *ep "  ","
.BI "bool reset_ep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device whose interface is being enabled
.IP "ep" 12
the endpoint
.IP "reset_ep" 12
flag to reset the endpoint state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Resets the endpoint state if asked, and sets dev->ep_{in,out} pointers.
For control endpoints, both the input and output sides are handled.
